sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This design will produce one of two necessary transcription factors for the HrpL AND gate. This will produce it in the presence of Sialic Acid
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: we wanted a Negative Feed Back loop
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39007
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the promoter sequence for the NanR transcription factor in the Nan Operon. This Operon is for Sialic Acid Degradation. Promoter is for E.Coli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This codes for the NanR Regulator. This is the the repressor for the Nan Operon and is turned off by the presence of sialic acid.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This allows the transport of Sialic Acid into the cell
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: These are the enzymes needed for Sialic Acid breakdown in E.Coli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Since these are all on an operon, we made sure there was sufficient space and an RBS in-between each coding region
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This codes for one of the two necessary genes (HrpS and HrpR) that will be needed to activate the HrpL AND gate
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel
